# Mission plan

**Execution model:** Squad Leader collects a developer-confirmed quick-fix bullet list, spawns a **Quick Fix Plan agent** that scaffolds a minimal parent plan and runs **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline. **`pr-plan`** spawns **`coding-session`** (¬ß5d). Ship execution stays on the detached **`coding-session`** lane; the Squad Leader tracks planning closure and ship progress, then proposes dispatch resolution.

**Skill reuse:** [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/) ‚Äî **`new-plan`**, **`pr-plan`**, **`coding-session`**. Spawn contracts: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md).

## Mission constraints (binding)

| Constraint | Rule |
|------------|------|
| **Scope** | Small fixes ‚Äî cosmetic UI/styling and **simple functional changes**; few lines per item |
| **Complexity** | **‚â§6** ‚Äî developer **must** only task this dispatch with low-complexity work |
| **Developer responsibility** | Developer confirms each dispatch item is complexity **6 or under** before opening; agent validates at intake |
| **Intake** | Short bullet list; items may be unrelated but each must qualify under scope and complexity |
| **PR count** | **Exactly one** PR plan per dispatch (single indexed child) |
| **Skipped** | Full **`author-prd`**, **`planner`** Master Plan, **`pr-breakdown`**, **`delivery-phases`**, **`phase-planner`** |
| **Out of scope redirect** | Complexity **>6**, multi-PR decomposition, or work needing Master Plan ‚Üí **`plan and deliver a single phase`** or **`plan and deliver`** (detached dispatch) |
| **Ship chain** | Same detached **`coding-session`** order as plan-and-deliver ¬ß8 |

### Operations filesystem invariant (binding)

All **`.sedea/operations/`** writes from the **main hosting clone** only ‚Äî see [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) ¬ß **Operations persistence (main hosting root only)**.

### Worktree removal ownership (binding)

Same as plan-and-deliver ‚Äî [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) ¬ß *Worktree ownership*; rule **20** ¬ß *Worktree removal ownership* in [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc).

## Objectives

1. **Quick-fix intake** ‚Äî Collect a developer-confirmed bullet list of small fixes (cosmetic UI/styling, copy tweaks, and simple functional changes) with complexity **‚â§6**.

2. **Single PR plan** ‚Äî Produce one PR plan under `.sedea/operations/` via minimal parent scaffold, **`new-plan`** (indexed child), and **`pr-plan`** inline (¬ß¬ß1‚Äì4 populated).

3. **Standard ship** ‚Äî Hand off to **`coding-session`** for implementation and the full plan-and-deliver ship chain (worktree, cut-point, deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, post-merge cleanup, optional plan-reconcile).

4. **Squad Leader oversight** ‚Äî Track planning completion and detached ship progress; gate **`MC_DISPATCH_RESOLVED_V1`**.

